This paper is primarily focused on video prediction using deep learning techniques, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of adversarial and perceptual loss functions also suggests a focus on generative models and image synthesis, which are common topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The evaluation of the model on a natural video dataset captured by car-mounted cameras suggests a focus on multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of a hierarchical architecture and top-down connections in the proposed model suggests a focus on neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category.
